WEBVTT

00:09.133 --> 00:10.833
Life--it's literally
all we have.

00:10.933 --> 00:11.867
But is it any good?

00:11.967 --> 00:13.200
I'm a reviewer,

00:13.300 --> 00:14.233
but I don't review

00:14.333 --> 00:15.867
food, books, or movies.

00:15.967 --> 00:17.967
I review life itself.

00:18.067 --> 00:19.567
[screams]

00:19.667 --> 00:21.500
[triumphant music]

00:21.600 --> 00:22.400
[parrot squawks]

00:22.500 --> 00:26.767
*

00:26.867 --> 00:28.000
Over here.

00:28.100 --> 00:32.200
*

00:33.733 --> 00:35.367
Welcome to Review.

00:35.467 --> 00:37.400
The sailor standing before you
is named Forrest MacNeil,

00:37.500 --> 00:39.033
and I am he.

00:39.133 --> 00:41.967
Ahoy, there's a mermaid
to my left,

00:42.067 --> 00:43.933
and her name is A.J. Gibbs.

00:44.033 --> 00:45.667
What a weird intro.

00:45.767 --> 00:46.800
Let's see what
we've got, eh?

00:46.900 --> 00:48.000
Yes.

00:48.100 --> 00:49.133
This next review
comes from a man

00:49.233 --> 00:52.667
or woman named Merle
from Plano, Texas.

00:52.767 --> 00:53.900
Okay.

00:54.000 --> 00:54.933
Hi there, Forrest,

00:55.033 --> 00:56.500
I've got four months left

00:56.600 --> 00:58.200
on a subscription
to an Internet dating website

00:58.300 --> 01:01.867
that has yielded me
exactly zero dates.

01:01.967 --> 01:04.667
What's it like
to catfish someone?

01:04.767 --> 01:06.067
- To catfish?
- Hmm.

01:06.133 --> 01:07.933
Well, I don't know
what that is,

01:08.067 --> 01:09.333
but I'm going to go find out,

01:09.433 --> 01:11.400
and then I'll review it.

01:12.500 --> 01:14.800
I'm sorry, what kind of fish
was it again?

01:14.900 --> 01:16.100
From what I understand,

01:16.200 --> 01:19.300
catfishing is
some kind of a prank,

01:19.400 --> 01:21.800
wherein one party,
the fisherman,

01:21.900 --> 01:25.900
creates a fake identity in order
to lure an unsuspecting party,

01:26.067 --> 01:27.433
the fisherman's cat,

01:27.533 --> 01:30.767
into falling in love
with this made-up phantom.

01:30.867 --> 01:32.300
That's ridiculous.

01:32.400 --> 01:33.867
Why would anybody
want to do that?

01:33.967 --> 01:36.367
(Forrest)
This review was sure
to be complicated by the fact

01:36.467 --> 01:39.900
that my father and I
were now living in my office

01:40.067 --> 01:40.767
because his first
and second homes

01:40.867 --> 01:43.100
had been freakishly destroyed.

01:43.200 --> 01:45.067
Aah!
We've got to get out of here!

01:45.100 --> 01:46.467
[explosion, screams]

01:46.567 --> 01:47.667
(Forrest)
And we were sharing the space

01:47.767 --> 01:50.167
with my intern, Josh,
and his girlfriend, Tina,

01:50.267 --> 01:51.933
who had been
squatting on my couch

01:52.067 --> 01:53.633
without permission for months.

01:53.733 --> 01:55.367
Seems like a crazy waste
of time for the catfisher.

01:55.467 --> 01:58.300
Well, when I've done it,
I've done it for power,

01:58.400 --> 02:01.400
for boredom, or, like,
when you just have 30 minutes

02:01.500 --> 02:03.967
before a thing
you have to be at.

02:04.067 --> 02:05.633
I just do it
'cause Tina does it.

02:05.733 --> 02:06.667
Is everybody done?

02:06.767 --> 02:08.333
Because one of us is
a life reviewer

02:08.433 --> 02:09.600
who has to go out
and have this experience

02:09.700 --> 02:13.100
and share special, universal
insights about it, okay?

02:13.200 --> 02:14.400
- [groans]
- That one is me.

02:14.500 --> 02:15.667
I'm the life reviewer.

02:15.767 --> 02:17.200
So, Lucille,
will you please give me

02:17.300 --> 02:18.933
the HTML website address

02:19.067 --> 02:20.800
for Googling things?

02:20.900 --> 02:22.200
We've been through this.

02:22.300 --> 02:24.067
Yes, I know.
You know what?

02:24.100 --> 02:24.933
I'll write it
on a Post-it this time

02:25.067 --> 02:27.500
and just keep it on my desk.

02:27.600 --> 02:28.133
W...

