02:54.733 --> 02:55.633
Okay.

02:55.733 --> 02:57.300
M.

02:57.400 --> 03:00.800
And what do I do?
I just type that into Google?

03:00.900 --> 03:02.200
Yep.

03:02.300 --> 03:03.600
Boy, she really
knows this stuff, huh?

03:03.700 --> 03:04.867
- She does, actually.
- Wow.

03:04.967 --> 03:06.333
- She's great.
- Wow.

03:06.433 --> 03:07.167
(Forrest)
To begin
my catfishing experience,

03:07.267 --> 03:09.067
I would first need my bait:

03:09.100 --> 03:10.933
a fraudulent profile.

03:11.067 --> 03:12.567
- How tall?
- Tall.

03:12.667 --> 03:14.567
(Forrest)
My roommates
insisted on helping,

03:14.667 --> 03:15.967
and they decided this fake man
should love children...

03:16.067 --> 03:18.400
- Kids and dogs.
- Like dogs...

03:18.500 --> 03:19.933
- Tolerate your cats.
- And tolerate your cats.

03:20.067 --> 03:22.267
- Be smart but not neurotic...
- Smart but not neurotic.

03:22.367 --> 03:23.700
- Outstanding in bed.
- Outstanding in the bedroom

03:23.800 --> 03:24.900
- but free of STDs.
- No STDs.

03:25.067 --> 03:26.667
- He's known heartbreak...
- Heartbreak...

03:26.767 --> 03:28.233
- But has no baggage.
- But he has no baggage.

03:28.333 --> 03:29.700
- Wow.
- God, beautiful.

03:29.800 --> 03:32.633
(Forrest)
In short,
this online Frankenstein monster

03:32.733 --> 03:34.900
was almost entirely the opposite
of Forrest MacNeil.

03:35.067 --> 03:36.333
No baggage.

03:36.433 --> 03:37.600
(Forrest)
But there was one other thing

03:37.700 --> 03:39.433
that I alone
would bestow upon him.

03:39.533 --> 03:43.267
May I please be the one
to say what his name is?

03:43.367 --> 03:46.267
And I knew
exactly what that name would be.

03:46.367 --> 03:48.933
The most popular classmate
in my fourth grade class

03:49.067 --> 03:52.633
was a boy impressively
named Charles Sweddington.

03:52.733 --> 03:55.067
Now, one day
Charles wore his father's

03:55.133 --> 03:56.567
Oscar de la Renta cologne
to school,

03:56.667 --> 04:00.533
and from that point forward,
he became known as Oscar.

04:00.633 --> 04:04.333
Oscar enjoyed his status
in our hierarchy

04:04.433 --> 04:06.433
for quite a while until
a Swedish exchange student

04:06.533 --> 04:09.700
with the delicious name
of Alvin Klassen arrived

04:09.800 --> 04:11.500
to make a play
for the throne.

04:11.600 --> 04:14.300
Now, by Christmas, Alvin
revealed himself to be deficient

04:14.400 --> 04:15.867
in several key regions
of the brain,

04:15.967 --> 04:18.467
including those responsible
for impulse control

04:18.567 --> 04:20.067
and where to put your hands,

04:20.133 --> 04:23.233
and the name Alvin
became synonymous with "weirdo."

04:23.333 --> 04:24.533
So Charles Sweddington,

04:24.633 --> 04:26.467
aka Oscar,
reclaimed his designation

04:26.567 --> 04:27.867
as our most popular student,

04:27.967 --> 04:29.967
and I, for one,
have never forgotten him.

04:30.067 --> 04:33.067
Now that it's time
to choose my nom de catfish,

04:33.167 --> 04:34.200
I know just what to do.

04:34.300 --> 04:38.233
- His name is Ace Shrift.
- [groans]

04:38.333 --> 04:40.967
It is an anagram
for "catfisher."

04:41.067 --> 04:43.600
You see, Charles Sweddington
appreciated an anagram

04:43.700 --> 04:46.067
more than anyone
I have ever known.

04:46.167 --> 04:47.500
He would love "Ace Shrift."

04:47.600 --> 04:51.367
There is one final capstone
to place on this monument

04:51.467 --> 04:52.567
to dishonesty.

04:52.667 --> 04:54.833
Ace Shrift is going
to need a face.

04:54.933 --> 04:58.933
(Forrest)
I did an image search
on www.google.com.

04:59.067 --> 05:02.067
"Very handsome man."

05:02.133 --> 05:05.133
Oh, plenty of
uncomplicated-looking dullards

05:05.233 --> 05:06.633
to choose from on here.

05:06.733 --> 05:09.100
Please allow me to borrow
your very handsome head.

05:09.200 --> 05:10.500
[chuckles]

05:10.600 --> 05:12.200
(Forrest)
45 minutes later,

05:12.300 --> 05:13.067
I had pasted
a handsome stranger's face

05:13.167 --> 05:15.500
to my dating profile,

05:15.600 --> 05:18.567
and I set my geographical
settings to "anywhere."

05:18.667 --> 05:22.600
So let's just go ahead
and go live, as they say.

05:22.700 --> 05:24.433
[chuckles]
Wow, look at that.

05:24.533 --> 05:25.700
(Forrest)
I was instantly matched

05:25.800 --> 05:27.333
with a number
of enticing ladies

05:27.433 --> 05:30.067
and several nut jobs
from all over the world.

05:30.133 --> 05:32.333
And then...

05:32.433 --> 05:33.600
Oh.

05:33.700 --> 05:35.700
[bleep].

05:35.800 --> 05:38.067
(Forrest)
To my utter astonishment,

05:38.133 --> 05:39.467
one of the sad sack ladies

05:39.567 --> 05:42.400
who matched with
the devilish cad, Ace Shrift,

05:42.500 --> 05:44.800
was my ex-wife, Suzanne.

05:44.900 --> 05:46.400
This was a stunning turn
of events,

05:46.500 --> 05:49.433
and I did not know
how Ace would handle it.

05:55.100 --> 05:55.967
(Forrest)
While searching for victims
for my catfish scheme,

05:56.067 --> 05:58.267
I somehow came across a woman

05:58.367 --> 06:01.067
whose user name
is NoJerksPlease

06:01.100 --> 06:03.267
but whose real name
is my ex-wife Suzanne,

06:03.367 --> 06:06.767
a woman I had loved dearly
but had to divorce

06:06.867 --> 06:09.300
so that others
might learn from my experience.

06:09.400 --> 06:10.633
You are gonna die alone!

06:10.733 --> 06:13.067
Let's not do this.
I don't want to be divorced.

06:13.100 --> 06:15.067
But even when I begged her
to take me back four times...

06:15.100 --> 06:16.167
Stop it.

06:16.267 --> 06:18.267
(Forrest)
She said no, no...

06:18.367 --> 06:19.400
- [bleep]!
- No and no.

06:19.500 --> 06:21.067
Sweetheart, don't--
Aah.

06:21.133 --> 06:23.467
(Forrest)
Although I have since
gotten over her completely,

06:23.567 --> 06:26.333
there was something delicious
about a little harmless payback.

06:26.433 --> 06:30.833
So here we go.
It's time to set the bait.

07:04.533 --> 07:07.233
Many times in my life
I have approached a woman

07:07.333 --> 07:10.733
and broken the ice
and been told to go away,

07:10.833 --> 07:12.767
but this, waiting with
the chance of no reply at all,

07:12.867 --> 07:15.400
is maddening.

07:15.500 --> 07:16.400
Has she received the message?

07:16.500 --> 07:17.667
'Cause her profile says

07:17.767 --> 07:19.667
that she has been online
since I sent it,

07:19.767 --> 07:21.067
but has she read it?

07:21.100 --> 07:23.400
And if she has,

07:23.500 --> 07:26.600
why is she rejecting Ace?

07:26.700 --> 07:29.333
Maybe she's not interested
in the opposite of me at all.

07:29.433 --> 07:31.800
I mean, maybe she--

07:31.900 --> 07:34.100
Oh.

07:34.200 --> 07:35.667
That's her.

07:35.767 --> 07:36.533
Oh, that's Suzanne.

07:36.633 --> 07:38.500
(Forrest)
I have to confess,

07:38.600 --> 07:41.333
I did feel a tinge of excitement
that she was interested in me--

07:41.433 --> 07:43.467
by which I mean Ace,
who does not exist.

07:43.567 --> 07:45.733
[laughs]

07:59.900 --> 08:03.267
(Forrest)
Deceiving Suzanne
in this way was exhilarating.

08:03.367 --> 08:05.300
She had broken my heart.

08:05.400 --> 08:07.933
She had refused to take me back,

08:08.067 --> 08:11.567
but now, Ace Shrift
had given me the upper hand.

08:11.667 --> 08:13.967
Ace was a cold-blooded fisherman

08:14.067 --> 08:15.967
out to catch
a warm-blooded fish,

08:16.067 --> 08:18.667
and I, Forrest, through Ace,

08:18.767 --> 08:21.467
saw an opportunity
to toy with her heart

08:21.567 --> 08:23.267
as she had toyed with mine.

08:23.367 --> 08:24.833
(Josh)
Mr. MacNeil!

08:24.933 --> 08:26.467
Close your stupid computer.

08:26.567 --> 08:28.200
Your face looks
like a scary nightlight.

08:28.300 --> 08:29.800
You're overplaying your hand.

08:29.900 --> 08:31.267
She's gonna think
you're desperate, okay?

08:31.367 --> 08:33.433
Shut your computer,
and go to sleep.

08:35.933 --> 08:38.767
(Forrest)
Catfishing was proving
to be a very satisfying pastime.

08:38.867 --> 08:41.500
(Tina)
Oh, God.

08:55.267 --> 08:56.467
(Forrest)
Over the next few days,

08:56.567 --> 08:59.167
Ace and Suzanne
became an online item.

08:59.267 --> 09:02.700
They chatted each and every day
and often deep into the night.

09:02.800 --> 09:06.467
Suzanne was falling for Ace,
and, truth be told,

09:06.567 --> 09:08.567
Ace was not unmoved.

09:08.667 --> 09:12.367
Then, a bombshell
dropped from the Internet.

09:15.300 --> 09:17.900
My catfish wants to Skype.
What is Skype?

09:18.067 --> 09:22.067
Oh, you're [bleep].

09:22.133 --> 09:24.067
What am I supposed to do?
I wouldn't be catfishing her

09:24.100 --> 09:26.800
if I'm sitting in front of my
computer looking at her, right?

09:26.900 --> 09:30.767
You've done
a reverse image search?

09:30.867 --> 09:31.867
What is that?

09:31.967 --> 09:32.600
Put the image in,
find out who that is?

09:32.700 --> 09:35.167
No!

09:35.267 --> 09:37.667
(Forrest)
I was now in the trickiest part
of catfishing,

09:37.767 --> 09:39.467
where you have to find
the handsome man

09:39.567 --> 09:41.933
whose picture you used
in your fake profile

09:42.067 --> 09:44.633
and persuade him
to Skype with your ex-wife.

09:44.733 --> 09:46.067
There he is.

09:46.167 --> 09:47.167
Oh.

09:47.267 --> 09:48.533
What?

09:48.633 --> 09:52.233
That's Joe Dale Jr.,
the baseball player.

09:52.333 --> 09:54.733
Thanks to
my complete ignorance

09:54.833 --> 09:56.367
of professional sports,
I had chosen the face

09:56.467 --> 10:00.033
of a shortstopman
for the Los Angeles Dodgers.

10:00.133 --> 10:01.133
[sighs]

10:01.233 --> 10:02.967
How about this place, huh?

10:03.067 --> 10:04.933
(Forrest)
On the bright side,
he was easy to locate

10:05.033 --> 10:06.900
