sorry, I feel like--

10:49.467 --> 10:50.700
- Up a little higher.
- No.

10:50.800 --> 10:52.200
- I'm good.
- Okay, all right.

10:52.300 --> 10:53.467
- Do you mind if I just--sorry.
- Nah.

10:53.567 --> 10:55.033
- I just--
- Nah.

10:55.133 --> 10:56.367
Argh, I just feel--
No, it's not perfect!

10:56.467 --> 10:57.533
Oh, oh, God! Okay.

10:57.633 --> 10:58.567
All right, real quick.

10:58.667 --> 11:01.200
You have a PhD
in animal husbandry,

11:01.300 --> 11:02.767
and you've never had an STD.

11:02.867 --> 11:05.067
Oh, and your favorite author
is Agatha Christie.

11:05.167 --> 11:06.400
[stammering]
Okay.

11:06.500 --> 11:07.100
Hey, beautiful.

11:07.200 --> 11:09.367
- Hello.
- Hi.

11:09.467 --> 11:10.600
(Joe)
Sorry, that's the TV.

11:10.700 --> 11:11.600
Let me shut that off.

11:14.467 --> 11:16.267
Um, I have to confess,

11:16.367 --> 11:19.267
I kind of didn't believe
you were real.

11:19.367 --> 11:21.667
I mean, "Ace Shrift"?

11:21.767 --> 11:23.233
You know that your name
is an anagram

11:23.333 --> 11:24.467
for "farce shit," right?

11:24.567 --> 11:26.367
Yeah, I did,
but you know what else?

11:26.467 --> 11:27.900
What?

11:28.067 --> 11:29.733
I wondered the same way
about you, you sexy lady.

11:29.833 --> 11:30.900
(Forrest)
I worried that Suzanne
would know right away

11:31.067 --> 11:33.300
that the grinning simpleton
on her computer

11:33.400 --> 11:36.933
could not possibly be the
charming and witty Mr. Shrift.

11:37.067 --> 11:40.100
But Suzanne, perhaps distracted
by the sight of an athlete

11:40.200 --> 11:41.533
in his underpants,

11:41.633 --> 11:43.733
